reviewText:
Foreword of advice: I suggest you search for videos on YouTube for a better idea on what the game is like, because, as always, a textual review accounts for very little and does not give a proper impression of what this (or any game, for that matter) is like. There is a demo available, you should probably check it out if you are interested in this game. Also, for a more intricate look into skills/stats/characters, feel free to visit a community wikia at http://sword-of-the-stars-the-pit.wikia.com/wiki/Main_Content

TD;DR #1: My opinion of this game - Amazing, even if with a few pretty major problems;

TL;DR #2: Short summary of impressions (Good points, Debatable poins, Negative points):
Good points:
+ Randomly generated - alot of replayability and variety in your gameplay, each game will be different; You will get your money's worth, if you like these sort of games;
+ Many character classes (as of Gold Edition - 8 + 1 secret character) - different strengths/weaknesses which must be accounted for;
+ Simple and functional graphics - this will run on a potato;
+ (personal) Gameplay - I enjoy these types of games and this is one of the few games that really nails it, think NetHack and you will probably understand what kind of game this is, minus the item interaction hilarity that NetHack had;
+ Bloody hard as nails;

Debatable points (these are as subjective as they can be):
+/- Relatively simplistic gameplay - I like the simplicity, but there's really not alot of nuance to it. Although many advocate that your skill (decision making) is more important, I do not believe it is so, as not finding any equipment by about mid-game is NOT salvagable by your skill;
+/- Randomly generated levels can dictate how easy/hard your game is going to be;
+/- Some characters are easier to play with - Some characters start out with psionic powers (Psion(Mindgames)/Seeker(Gold Edition)). This allows them to be less dependant on luck and more dependant on skill due to having all the tools necessary (Psionic powers in this case), which allows them to be less dependant on equipment for starting levels;

Negative points:
- Each run will require alot of time to play - clearing even 10 floors can easily take about 2 hours for me (as I have a tendency of trying to clear the whole floor) and as you go deeper, each  level requires more time, due to stronger enemies, unless you are fortunate with your gear;
- This game features unlockable recipes (crafting), which you get from Consoles. Unlocking all recipes (or some potent ones) will require alot of time grinding". This game does not require crafting to win
